He is absolutely correct. We quite often name diseases based on their origin or epicenter. Why is it suddenly racist here? Is it because it's Trump? Is it because the media is beholden to China?
Spanish Flu (Spain)
West Nile Virus (West Nile, Uganda)
Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (Middle East)
Lyme Disease (Lyme, CT)
Rocky Mountain Spotted Fever (Rocky Mountains, North America)
Ross River Fever (Ross River, Queensland, Australia)
Omsk Hemorrhagic Fever (Omsk, Russia)
Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever (Ebola River, Africa)
Valley Fever (San Joaquin Valley, CA)
Marburg Virus Disease (Marburg, Germany)
Norovirus / Norwalk Virus (Norwalk, OH)
Zika Fever (Zika Forest, Uganda)
Japanese Encephalitis (Japan)
German Measles (Germany)
Lassa Fever (Lassa, Nigeria)
